This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) category as it deals with learning video representations for tasks such as action recognition and zero or few-shot learning. The use of an evolutionary search algorithm to find optimal combinations of loss functions suggests that it could also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) category. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of unsupervised representation learning, which could place it in the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) category. The use of distribution matching and Zipf's law suggests that it could also belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) category. Finally, the paper mentions the evaluation of the proposed method using an unsupervised constraint, which could place it in the Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) category.
